## Licenses
% use Cavil::ReportUtil qw(hard_incompatibilities);
% my $hard = hard_incompatibilities($report->{license_compatibility} // {});
% if (@$hard) {
%   my %by; push @{$by{$_->[0]}}, $_->[1] for @$hard;

Note: the OSADL compatibility matrix flags these license combinations as incompatible when combined
into a single work. Whether that applies depends on how the components are combined or merely
aggregated; the full directional matrix with OSADL's explanations is in the web report.
%   for my $lic (sort keys %by) {
* <%== $lic %>: <%== join(', ', @{$by{$lic}}) %>
%   }

% }
% if (@{$report->{missed_files}}) {

Note: Report is incomplete, reviewers need to create new license patterns for unmatched keywords or ignore false
